sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
This Action updates the user attributes in AD.

Inputs:

  • User Name - one of the following properties of the user you wish to look up
    • SAM Account Name
    • GUID - A unique identifier for an AD object
    • SID(Security Identifier) - A binary value that specifies the security identifier (SID) of the user. The SID is a unique value used to identify the user as a security principal.
  • First Name
  • Last Name
  • Display Name
  • Email Address
  • Mobile Phone
  • Job Title
  • Department
  • Street Address
  • City
  • State
  • Country - This property has to be a ISO-3166 Alpha-2 code
  • Manager
  • Office Location
  • Home Directory

If the user or manager does not exist, Error will be thrown.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to “Success" if the request succeeds or “Error" if a failure in AD occurs.
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • User does not exist
  • Invalid Credentials for host
  • Invalid hostname in connection or Host not reachable from Mid server
  • Unknown Error. Please check error log for more information

To use this action, a corresponding AD Connection and Credential must be created and associated with the AD Connection & Credential Alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More

sys_hub_action_type_snapshot.description:
This Action updates the user attributes in AD.

Inputs:

  • User Name - one of the following properties of the user you wish to look up
    • SAM Account Name
    • GUID - A unique identifier for an AD object
    • SID(Security Identifier) - A binary value that specifies the security identifier (SID) of the user. The SID is a unique value used to identify the user as a security principal.
  • First Name
  • Last Name
  • Display Name
  • Email Address
  • Mobile Phone
  • Job Title
  • Department
  • Street Address
  • City
  • State
  • Country - This property has to be a ISO-3166 Alpha-2 code
  • Manager
  • Office Location
  • Home Directory

If the user or manager does not exist, Error will be thrown.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to “Success" if the request succeeds or “Error" if a failure in AD occurs.
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • User does not exist
  • Invalid Credentials for host
  • Invalid hostname in connection or Host not reachable from Mid server
  • Unknown Error. Please check error log for more information

To use this action, a corresponding AD Connection and Credential must be created and associated with the AD Connection & Credential Alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More
